  <div class="text">
    <p>Flying is the most convenient way to travel long distances that would otherwise take hours and days. When flying, we don’t perceive distances as much as time spent or lost.</p>
    <p>While travelling, local arrival time is usually more important than time at home. If you arrive in New York at midnight, you usually go to bed, despite being 9pm at home, in Los Angeles.</p>
    <p>Below are maps of the US from the point of view of major cities. To create these maps , we simply substracted the local arrival time by the local departure time of all US flights for a full week.</p>

    <h2 class="section-title">East vs West</h2>
    <p>The Atlantic and Pacific coasts are ones of the most populated regions in the United States. Hundred of flights per day fly between the coasts, crossing three time zones.</p>
